This paper proposes a new type of recurrent neural network (RNN) that addresses the well-known gradient vanishing and exploding problems and allows for the learning of long-term dependencies. As such, it is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing), cs.LG (machine learning), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), cs.CV (computer vision), and cs.CL (computation and language).
